## 📌 Project Overview

The **Library Management System** is a SQL-based database project designed to streamline library operations through efficient data management and reporting.

This project demonstrates practical SQL skills including database design, CRUD operations, advanced querying, stored procedures, business reporting, and data analysis.

The system manages:

* 📖 Book Inventory
* 👥 Library Members
* 🏢 Branch Operations
* 👨‍💼 Employee Management
* 🔄 Book Issue & Return Tracking
* 💰 Rental Revenue Analysis

---

## 🎯 Business Objectives

* Maintain accurate records of books, members, employees, and branches.
* Track issued and returned books.
* Monitor book availability in real time.
* Generate branch performance reports.
* Identify overdue books and active members.
* Analyze rental revenue and book demand.
* Automate issue and return processes using stored procedures.

---

## 🏗️ Database Schema

The database consists of six interconnected tables:

| Table Name    | Purpose                              |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Branch        | Stores library branch information    |
| Employees     | Maintains employee records           |
| Members       | Contains member registration details |
| Books         | Tracks library inventory             |
| Issued_Status | Records issued book transactions     |
| Return_Status | Records returned book transactions   |

### Entity Relationships

* One Branch ➜ Many Employees
* One Member ➜ Multiple Book Issues
* One Book ➜ Multiple Transactions
* One Issue Transaction ➜ One Return Transaction

